CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 17, 1950, pg. 7 reads: "Republicans Elect Chairman In Fifth Ward - ...Center: The Rev. Cornell Talley is hesitatingly grasping for most effective words in nominating Dr. Winstead, who opposed Thompkins at request of L. Pat McGrath, Curtis Haines and the Rev. Mr. Talley..."
TitMainTitle: Rev. Cornell Talley standing in front of stage in A. Leo Weil school auditorium, with three men gathered around table on stage with curtains and tree backdrop, for Fifth Ward elections
